==English==
===Etymology===
There are several theories of the origin of this expression.

One is that it resembles other English dialectical shortenings like "sorta" or "kinda".  It is thus a contraction of "hell of".  This fits with the way it is used: i.e. "Norcal is hella awesome".

Another is that it is derived from [[Hell]] + [[of]] + [[a]], slang originating in the San Francisco Bay Area in the early 1980s, now used commonly by youths from the [[West Coast]].  The origins of the word itself are unknown, but some presume it to have started as a slang way of saying "Hell of A" by [[Mexican]] Americans.  This, however, is not true because many Northern Californians regardless of race use hella frequently.  It has lately become a [[shibboleth]] for people from [[Northern California]] as well as a point of local pride; for instance, with a t-shirt reading "Norcal is hella awesome!" In Northern California the word is only used as an adverb or adjective.

===Adverb===
'''hella'''
# [[very|Very]], an [[intensifier]] of adjectives in their absolute form.
#:"I guess she seems '''hella''' stoned in her commercial and I have a thing for chicks that are stoned and/or drunk."[http://www.davezdyrko.com/babes/120902.html]
#:"I've been a Star Wars fan since I was '''hella''' young[.]"[http://www.xanga.com/home.aspx?user=krazychowmein]
# [[much|Much]], an intensifier of adjectives in their [[comparative]] form.
#:"[I]f next gen games look better than the current best PC games, then they will look '''hella''' better than the current Xbox games."[http://www.xboxaddict.com/forums/archive/index.php/t-69399.html]
# An intesifier of verbs.
#:"...eena was driving away, and the door was open, so i '''hella''' ran for it[...]"[http://www.nutang.com/bliss/weblog/covered_in_rain10/&exhume=5]
#:"Oh.. today's Cyrell's bday.. '''we hella sang her happy birthday at the spot'''..."[http://www.xanga.com/home.aspx?user=jtljc_RG]

===Adjective===
'''hella'''
# [[real|Real]], an intensifier of nouns.
#:"hope the LOCAL YOKALS<!-- sic --> didnt give u guys too hard of a time they can be '''hella''' assholes"[http://hardcoreforthepeople.com/forum/viewtopic.php?p=23345&sid=a5da5aff2c41b1f07b9c939a4239d46b]

===Contraction===
'''hella'''
# [[Hell]] [[of]] [[a]].
#:2002:"I've got a '''hella''' lot of travel over the next few weeks."[http://www.coffeekid.com/cafetalk/09-19-2002]
#:2005:"It started to rain, and if anyone remembers from my previous post, how much i love Rock and Rain together. So it was going to be a '''hella''' time."[http://www.insidepulse.com/ubbthreads/showflat.php?Cat=&Number=49998&Main=36997]
#:2003:"The plaintiffs got $1 million in compensatory damages and $145 million in punitive damages.  That’s a '''hella''' lot of damages."[http://lawschool.mikeshecket.com/civpro/11-10-03.htm]

===Interjection===
'''hella'''
#[[for sure|For sure]], used to affirm what was just said.
#:"We definitely rocked that shit man!" "'''Hella'''!"

